2017-18 Men's Swimming Roster

Choose a Player:

Nicholas Brown

Height 6-0

Class Junior

Bio

Biography

AS A JUNIOR (2017-18)

Did not compete due to injury.

PREVIOUS EXPEREICNE

Swam for Neil Harper and Kirk Hampleman at Florida State…Held the fastest 400 IM on the team as a freshman…Assisted the team in a second-place finish in the tri-meet against Duke and Virginia Tech.

HIGH SCHOOL

USA Swimming Junior and Senior National Qualifier under Adam Byars…Swam for Jason Lucey at Greenbrier HS…Named team MVP form his sophomore through his senior year…CSRA Swimmer of the Year during his junior and senior year…FHSAA State Champion in the 100 breaststroke and runner-up in the 200 IM…Also placed in the top-16 in the state in the 200 medley and 400 freestyle relay teams…Hold the school records in the 500, 100, 200 and 500 freestyle, 100 fly, 100 breaststroke, 200 IM and as a member of the 200 freestyle, 400 freestyle and 200 medley relays.

CLUB

Swam for Martin Zubero at Episcopal Amberjax Swimming where he qualified for the Senior National and US Open Qualifier…2016 Southern Zone Champion in the 200 breaststroke...Also placed third in the 400 IM and fifth in the 200 IM.

PERSONAL

Majoring in Finance…Most memorable athletic achievement in winning the FSHAA State Championship in the 100 breast and Sectional Championship in the 200 breast…Names his grandfather the most influential in his life…Favorite food is sushi…Names Matthew McConaughey as favorite actor Roger Federer and Russel Westbrook as favorite athletes…Favorite sports teams are FSU Football, Jacksonville Jaguars and OKC Thunder…Born in Jacksonville, Fla…Son of David and Leonarda Brown and has a brother, Kyle.
